APPLIED ENERGISTICS 2

Applied Smelting is an independent add-on for Applied Energistics 2 (AE2).
AE2 is developed by the Applied Energistics team and is distributed under its
own licenses. AE2 is a separate runtime dependency and is not included in the
Applied Smelting JAR.

The ME Smelting Terminal model geometry is adapted from AE2's ME Terminal
monitor model (assets/ae2/models/part/monitor_base.json in AE2 26.1.10-beta).
The original model is copyright the Applied Energistics contributors and is
licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 3.0. Applied Smelting's modified model and original
smelting-specific textures are distributed under the same license.

The ME Smelter and ME Smelting Terminal recipes are adapted from AE2's ME Drive
and ME Crafting Terminal recipes respectively. They are modified to incorporate
a Minecraft furnace and are distributed under Applied Smelting's code/data
license.

Any exact, unmodified AE2 files retained locally for development reference are
not part of Applied Smelting and are excluded from version control.

